Share this on WhatsAppSpread the loveThe President Federal Republic of Nigeria President Muhammadu Buhari is set to visit Ogun State on Thursday, January 13.
In a statement issued by Kunle Somorin, the Chief Press Secretary to Ogun State Governor, Dapo Abiodun, he stated that during the visit, the President will inaugurate some of the infrastructural projects executed by the governor.
According to the statement, the President will be welcomed at the Gateway City Gate Monument Park, Sagamu Interchange, at 10am, where the first project will be commissioned by him.
Apart from the Gateway City Gate, other projects expected to be inaugurated by President Buhari include Ijebu-Ode Mojoda-Epe expressway and two housing estates – the 527-Unit low and Medium Kobape Housing scheme Kobape and the Highbrow, 83 duplexes at Kings Court Estate at Oke Mosan, Abeokuta.
The governor’s spokesman stated that invited guests are expected to be seated by 9.30am at the City Gate by the Sagamu Interchange and Abeokuta expressway while observing all COVID-19 safety protocols.
